President Donald Trump hosted frontline responders from the Atlanta Fire Rescue Department, Atlanta Police Department, and Georgia State Patrol to thank them for their bravery and service during a fire on Interstate 85 that resulted in a bridge collapse. The firefighters, police officers, and state patrol officers were recognized for their efforts in preventing any fatalities during the incident. The U.S. Department of Transportation approved $10 million in emergency relief funds to assist in repairing the bridge, which is scheduled to reopen by June 15, 2017. Governor Nathan Deal praised the troopers and first responders for their commendable actions during the incident.